Petr Baudis is a UNIX programmer. In the past, he maintained e.g.
the ELinks web browser, was one of the core developers of the Git
version control system and contributed regularly to projects such as
the GNU libc library, strategy game OpenTTD, etc. Currently, he works
as an independent software consultant focusing mainly on system
programming.  He also teaches few diverse courses at the Faculty of
Mathematics and Physics, Charles University and spends his evenings
doing research in the field of Computer Go and soldering at
the Prague hackerspace brmlab.
